# ============================================================================
# FORMAT B — PREVIOUS v2 PROPOSAL
# Distinct markers per interaction: $DIALOGUE $GRAMMAR $EXERCISE $QUIZ $MATCH
# $DICTATION $RESPOND $CHAT. ($QUIZ=select, $MATCH=pair, $EXERCISE=reveal drill,
# $RESPOND=LLM-graded, $DICTATION=write.)
# ============================================================================

$MODULE
DIOCO_DOC_ID: lc_alc_lla_bk4_l1a
TITLE: ALC Book 4 — Lesson 1A: Sports and Games
DESCRIPTION: Talking about sports, games, and where people live (past and present).
TARGET_LANG_G: en
HOME_LANG_G: en
VOICE_DEFAULT: aoede | Clear, friendly American English narrator

$LESSON Lesson 1A

# --- Figure 1: repeat vocabulary ---
$DIALOGUE Figure 1: Sports and Games
INTRO: Look at the pictures and repeat the words and sentences.
INSTRUCTION: Listen and repeat.

VOCAB: play / game / ball
VOCAB_T: играть / игра / мяч
IMAGE: page_007_001.jpg
LINE: The children play a game with their ball.
LINE_T: Дети играют в игру со своим мячом.

VOCAB: football
VOCAB_T: американский футбол
IMAGE: page_007_002.jpg
LINE: Sam plays football every day.
LINE_T: Сэм играет в футбол каждый день.

VOCAB: baseball
VOCAB_T: бейсбол
IMAGE: page_007_003.jpg
LINE: George plays baseball on weekends.
LINE_T: Джордж играет в бейсбол по выходным.

VOCAB: tennis
VOCAB_T: теннис
IMAGE: page_007_004.jpg
LINE: They play tennis after class.
LINE_T: Они играют в теннис после занятий.

VOCAB: soccer
VOCAB_T: футбол (соккер)
IMAGE: page_007_005.jpg
LINE: Carlos plays soccer on Saturdays.
LINE_T: Карлос играет в футбол по субботам.

VOCAB: basketball
VOCAB_T: баскетбол
IMAGE: page_007_006.jpg
LINE: Carl plays basketball at school.
LINE_T: Карл играет в баскетбол в школе.

# --- Figure 2: match each sentence to a picture ($MATCH) ---
$MATCH Figure 2: Which sport?
INTRO: Listen to each sentence and match it to the correct picture.
INSTRUCTION: Match the sentence to the picture.

OPTION_IMAGE: a | page_008_001.jpg
OPTION_IMAGE: b | page_008_002.jpg
OPTION_IMAGE: c | page_008_003.jpg
OPTION_IMAGE: d | page_008_004.jpg
OPTION_IMAGE: e | page_008_005.jpg
OPTION_IMAGE: f | page_008_006.jpg

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: Tony and Jim watch soccer games on TV.
ANSWER: e

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: Betty and Jane are playing tennis.
ANSWER: d

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: Mark plays baseball.
ANSWER: c

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: My children play with a ball after school.
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: The basketball game is at eight o'clock tonight.
ANSWER: f

# --- Figure 3: hear Q&A, circle the matching statement ($QUIZ) ---
$QUIZ Figure 3: Likes and doesn't like
INTRO: Listen to each short conversation, then choose the sentence that is true.
INSTRUCTION: Circle the correct sentence.

PROMPT: John, do you like football games? — No, I don't.
OPTION: a | John likes football games.
OPTION: b | John doesn't like football games.
ANSWER: b
FEEDBACK: John doesn't like football games.

PROMPT: Jack and Joe, do you like sports? — Yes, we do.
OPTION: a | Jack and Joe like sports.
OPTION: b | Jack and Joe don't like sports.
ANSWER: a
FEEDBACK: Jack and Joe like sports.

PROMPT: Mr. Adams, do you like basketball? — Yes, I do.
OPTION: a | Mr. Adams likes basketball.
OPTION: b | Mr. Adams doesn't like basketball.
ANSWER: a
FEEDBACK: Mr. Adams likes basketball.

PROMPT: Do you like baseball? — No, we don't.
OPTION: a | They like baseball.
OPTION: b | They don't like baseball.
ANSWER: b
FEEDBACK: They don't like baseball.

PROMPT: Donna, do you like tennis? — Yes, I do.
OPTION: a | Donna likes tennis.
OPTION: b | Donna doesn't like tennis.
ANSWER: a
FEEDBACK: Donna likes tennis.

# --- Figure 4: answer the questions ($EXERCISE: prompt -> reveal response) ---
$EXERCISE Figure 4: Answer the questions
INTRO: Listen to the statement and question, answer out loud, then reveal the model answer.
INSTRUCTION: Answer, then check.

EXAMPLE
PROMPT: The children play ball in the afternoon. What do the children like to do in the afternoon?
PROMPT_T: Дети играют в мяч во второй половине дня. Что дети любят делать днём?
RESPONSE: The children like to play ball in the afternoon.
RESPONSE_T: Дети любят играть в мяч во второй половине дня.

PROMPT: Sue and Kate go to football games on weekends. What do Sue and Kate like to do on weekends?
RESPONSE: They like to go to football games on weekends.

PROMPT: Jim swims at the base on Saturdays. What does Jim like to do on Saturdays?
RESPONSE: Jim likes to swim at the base on Saturdays.

PROMPT: Mr. and Mrs. Adams play tennis every morning. What do Mr. and Mrs. Adams like to do every morning?
RESPONSE: Mr. and Mrs. Adams like to play tennis every morning.

PROMPT: Jack watches basketball on Fridays. What does Jack like to watch on Fridays?
RESPONSE: Jack likes to watch basketball on Fridays.

# --- Figure 5: repeat sentences (map) ---
$DIALOGUE Figure 5: Cities and Towns in Texas
INTRO: Look at the map of Texas and repeat the words and sentences.
INSTRUCTION: Listen and repeat.
IMAGE: page_010_001.jpg

VOCAB: city / cities
VOCAB_T: город / города
LINE: Texas has big cities and small towns.
LINE_T: В Техасе есть большие города и маленькие городки.

VOCAB: town
VOCAB_T: городок
LINE: The King family lives in a small town.
LINE_T: Семья Кинг живёт в маленьком городке.

VOCAB: lives
VOCAB_T: живёт
LINE: The Soto family lives in the city of Dallas.
LINE_T: Семья Сото живёт в городе Даллас.

LINE: Sometimes, the King family visits the Soto family in Dallas.
LINE_T: Иногда семья Кинг навещает семью Сото в Далласе.

LINE: Los Angeles, New York and Chicago are also big cities. These cities are not in Texas.
LINE_T: Лос-Анджелес, Нью-Йорк и Чикаго тоже большие города. Эти города не в Техасе.

# --- Figure 6: hear a question, circle the answer ($QUIZ) ---
$QUIZ Figure 6: Choose the correct answer
INTRO: Listen to each question and choose the correct answer.
INSTRUCTION: Circle the correct answer.

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: My sister has a house in San Antonio. She works in San Antonio. What does she do in San Antonio?
OPTION: a | She works in San Antonio.
OPTION: b | She plays sports in San Antonio.
ANSWER: a
FEEDBACK: She works in San Antonio.

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: Joe lives in New York City. Where does he live?
OPTION: a | He lives in a small town.
OPTION: b | He lives in a big city.
ANSWER: b
FEEDBACK: He lives in a big city.

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: Jacksonville is not on the map. It's very small. Is it a city or a town?
OPTION: a | It's a town.
OPTION: b | It's a city.
ANSWER: a
FEEDBACK: It's a town.

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: Mary is at her friend's house. They are talking. What's Mary doing?
OPTION: a | Mary is sleeping.
OPTION: b | Mary is visiting her friend.
ANSWER: b
FEEDBACK: Mary is visiting her friend.

# --- Figure 7: sound discrimination J vs Y ($QUIZ + AUDIO_ONLY) ---
$QUIZ Figure 7: /j/ as in "jet" or /y/ as in "yet"?
INTRO: Listen to each word. Circle a for the /j/ sound (as in "jet") or b for the /y/ sound (as in "yet").
INSTRUCTION: Circle the sound you hear.

EXAMPLE
AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: jam
OPTION: a | /j/ — jet
OPTION: b | /y/ — yet
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: joke
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: year
ANSWER: b

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: you
ANSWER: b

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: jaw
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: join
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: yes
ANSWER: b

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: yard
ANSWER: b

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: juice
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: jay
ANSWER: a

AUDIO_ONLY
PROMPT: use
ANSWER: b

# --- Figure 8: listening passage + comprehension (ONE figure -> TWO activities) ---
$DIALOGUE Figure 8: Linda's Week
INTRO: Listen to the paragraph about Linda.
INSTRUCTION: Listen.
IMAGE: page_012_001.jpg
SPEAKER: Narrator
LINE: This is Linda. Linda works in an office. She works from Monday to Friday — she works all week long. On Saturdays, Linda gets up early and cleans her house all morning long. After she cleans, she starts to cook. She likes to cook a big dinner for her friends; she starts to cook the meal at 2 p.m. and cooks all afternoon long. Her friends come at 6:30. Sometimes they watch a show on TV, and sometimes they talk. Linda likes their visits very much.
LINE_T: Это Линда. Линда работает в офисе. Она работает с понедельника по пятницу — всю неделю. По субботам Линда встаёт рано и всё утро убирает дом. После уборки она начинает готовить. Она любит готовить большой ужин для друзей; она начинает готовить в 2 часа дня и готовит весь день. Друзья приходят в 6:30. Иногда они смотрят телепередачу, иногда разговаривают. Линде очень нравятся их визиты.

$QUIZ Figure 8: Linda's Week — comprehension
INTRO: Listen again and choose the correct word for each sentence.
INSTRUCTION: Circle the correct word.

PROMPT: Linda works ____.
OPTION: a | all night long
OPTION: b | all week long
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: On Saturdays, she ____ her house.
OPTION: a | cleans
OPTION: b | cooks
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: She ____ a big dinner, and she ____ to cook the meal at 2:00.
OPTION: a | cooks / starts
OPTION: b | cleans / ends
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: Sometimes they watch a ____ on TV.
OPTION: a | game
OPTION: b | show
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: Linda likes her friends' ____ very much.
OPTION: a | visits
OPTION: b | houses
ANSWER: a
